item.title: What is a set?
item.description: TL;DR A set is an unordered collection of distinct objects Two sets are equal if they have exactly the same elements The size of a set is called cardinality; there exists finite and infinite sets A is a subset of B, if every element of A is also an element of B I am a set with no elements, Yet I am not empty. What am I? Answer: A set.
